This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) category as it deals with session-based recommendation, which is a subfield of recommendation systems. The paper also discusses a probabilistic framework for modeling user behavior, which is a common approach in machine learning and falls under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. Additionally, the paper uses computational techniques such as the re-parameterization trick and variational auto-encoder, which are commonly used in Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the correlation between items and their popularity, which is a topic that falls under the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category.
